    "problemStatement": "Given a positive integer NNN, construct two arrays AAA and BBB, each of size NNN such that:\n\n\nAi\u2260AjA_i \\ne A_jAi\u200b\ue020=Aj\u200b for all (1\u2264i&lt;j\u2264N)(1\\le i \\lt j \\le N)(1\u2264i&lt;j\u2264N);\nBi\u2260BjB_i \\ne B_jBi\u200b\ue020=Bj\u200b for all (1\u2264i&lt;j\u2264N)(1\\le i \\lt j \\le N)(1\u2264i&lt;j\u2264N);\nAi\u2260BjA_i \\ne B_jAi\u200b\ue020=Bj\u200b for all (1\u2264i,j\u2264N)(1\\le i,j \\le N)(1\u2264i,j\u2264N);\n1\u2264Ai,Bi\u22643\u22c51051 \\leq A_i, B_i \\leq 3\\cdot 10^51\u2264Ai\u200b,Bi\u200b\u22643\u22c5105 for all (1\u2264i\u2264N)(1\\leq i \\leq N)(1\u2264i\u2264N);\n\u2295A[1,i]=\u2295B[1,i]\\oplus A[1,i] = \\oplus B[1,i]\u2295A[1,i]=\u2295B[1,i] for all (1\u2264i\u2264N)(1\\le i \\le N)(1\u2264i\u2264N) such that iii is **even**.\nHere \u2295A[L,R]\\oplus A[L,R]\u2295A[L,R] corresponds to the bitwise XOR of all elements of the subarray [L,R][L,R][L,R] of array AAA. Similarly, \u2295B[L,R]\\oplus B[L,R]\u2295B[L,R] corresponds to the bitwise XOR of all elements of the subarray [L,R][L,R][L,R] of array BBB.\n\nIf multiple answers are possible, ouput any.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nFirst line will contain TTT, the number of test cases. Then the test cases follow.\nEach test case contains of a single line of input, a single integer NNN - as mentioned in statement.\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output two lines.\n\n\n\nThe first line contains NNN space-separated integers denoting the elements of the array AAA.\nThe second line contains NNN space-separated integers denoting the elements of the array BBB.\n\nIf multiple answers are possible, ouput any.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u226410001 \\leq T \\leq 10001\u2264T\u22641000",
